WEBVTT

01:15.630 --> 01:19.498
by
HOME BOX OFFICE

01:19.500 --> 01:23.618
A Division of TIME WARNER
ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY, LP.

02:52.500 --> 02:55.128
I REMEMBER IT ALL
VERY WELL LOOKING BACK

02:55.130 --> 02:57.428
IT WAS THE SUMMER
I TURNED 18

02:57.430 --> 02:59.796
WE LIVED IN A ONE-ROOM,
RUNDOWN SHACK

02:59.800 --> 03:02.360
ON THE OUTSKIRTS
OF NEW ORLEANS

03:02.360 --> 03:04.419
WE DIDN'T HAVE
MONEY FOR FOOD

03:04.430 --> 03:06.591
( female )
SO, I WANT YOU TO MEET THIS GUY
I'M GOING OUT WITH TONIGHT,

03:06.600 --> 03:08.329
OKAY ?

03:10.800 --> 03:13.360
HE'S KIND OF A DORK,
BUT IN A SWEET WAY.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.658
HE SEEMS REAL
AT LEAST.

03:15.660 --> 03:18.857
AND HE'S KINDA
RICH I THINK.

03:18.860 --> 03:19.952
KINDA.

03:19.960 --> 03:22.121
OF COURSE,
SO WAS KADEEM,

03:22.130 --> 03:24.826
AND THAT WAS A FUCKING WASTE
OF TWO YEARS OF MY LIFE.

03:29.530 --> 03:31.157
YOU KNOW WHAT ?

03:31.160 --> 03:33.628
I KNEW YOU NEVER
LIKED KADEEM.

03:33.630 --> 03:36.622
SO, I'M GONNA BRING THIS GUY
HOME TO MEET YOU.

03:36.630 --> 03:38.427
AND THIS TIME,

03:38.430 --> 03:42.526
I SWEAR I WILL PAY ATTENTION
TO WHAT YOU THINK.

03:44.030 --> 03:48.558
BECAUSE I AM ONE FUCKING
HOT-SHIT BITCH

03:48.560 --> 03:50.858
AND HE'D BE
FUCKING LUCKY TO HAVE ME.

04:01.100 --> 04:04.297
SHE LOOKED AT
OUR PITIFUL SHACK,
THEN SHE LOOKED AT ME

04:08.930 --> 04:10.557
OH...

04:10.560 --> 04:13.950
OH, DOES THAT FEEL GOOD.

04:20.630 --> 04:21.892
HEY, TITO !

04:21.900 --> 04:24.721
COME HANG
WITH ME, OKAY ?

04:25.630 --> 04:27.029
( meowing )

04:27.030 --> 04:30.158
THANK YOU.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.427
WHO'S MY LOVER ?

04:32.430 --> 04:33.920
YES.

04:37.030 --> 04:38.827
YES.

04:38.830 --> 04:40.889
AREN'T YOU GLAD
I RESCUED YOU ?

04:40.900 --> 04:43.118
YOU BETTER BE
FUCKING GLAD.

04:43.130 --> 04:45.655
COST ME 800 BUCKS
IN VET BILLS.

04:45.660 --> 04:47.298
AT A TIME
WHEN THINGS

04:47.300 --> 04:50.292
WERE PARTICULARLY TIGHT
FOR MOMMY, I MIGHT ADD.

04:52.900 --> 04:54.754
ONE GOOD THING
ABOUT THIS GUY TONIGHT,

04:54.760 --> 04:58.719
HE'S GOT A BIG FAT DICK
AND HE FUCKS LIKE A JACKHAMMER.

05:03.500 --> 05:05.024
THOSE NEVER LAST.

05:16.560 --> 05:18.425
LORD FORGIVE ME
FOR WHAT I DO

05:18.430 --> 05:21.149
BUT IF YOU WANT OUT,
IT'S UP TO YOU

05:21.160 --> 05:24.425
DON'T LET ME DOWN,
YOUR MOMMA'S GONNA HELP YOU
MOVE UPTOWN

05:34.160 --> 05:38.790
( choir singing )

05:56.660 --> 05:59.197
(singing )

06:09.560 --> 06:11.494
( singing continues )

06:16.800 --> 06:19.758
DAVID, I'M SO GLAD
TO SEE YOU HERE.

06:19.760 --> 06:22.320
IT'S ALWAYS NICE WHEN SOMEONE
COMES BACK TO THE FOLD.

06:22.330 --> 06:23.820
OH, I'VE BEEN
GOING TO CHURCH.

06:23.830 --> 06:26.390
I WAS JUST GOING
TO A DIFFERENT CHURCH.

06:26.400 --> 06:28.095
REALLY,
WHICH ONE ?

06:28.100 --> 06:29.249
ST. STEPHEN'S ?

06:29.260 --> 06:30.420
IN THE PALISADES ?

06:30.430 --> 06:32.489
NO, ST. STEPHEN'S
IN WEST HOLLYWOOD.

06:32.500 --> 06:36.948
WELL, I HOPE YOU ALWAYS
FEEL AS WELCOME HERE

06:36.960 --> 06:38.598
AS YOU DID THERE.

06:38.600 --> 06:40.249
THAN KS.

06:40.260 --> 06:41.750
YOU KNOW, YOUR FATHER
WAS A DEACON HERE

06:41.760 --> 06:43.296
AND WE STILL HAVEN'T
REPLACED HIM.

06:43.300 --> 06:45.052
I THINK IT WOULD BE GOOD
FOR THIS CHURCH

06:45.060 --> 06:46.755
TO LISTEN TO
A YOUNGER VOICE.

06:46.760 --> 06:48.250
IF YOU'RE
AT ALL INTERESTED,

06:48.260 --> 06:50.023
I COULD SUBMIT YOUR NAME
TO THE BISHOP.

06:50.030 --> 06:52.396
ME ?
A DEACON ?

06:52.400 --> 06:54.356
DAVID,
TH'S WONDERFUL.

06:54.360 --> 06:56.328
YOUR FATHER
WOULD BE SO PROUD.

06:56.330 --> 06:59.219
WELL, SURE, I'D BE HONORED
TO BE CONSIDERED.

06:59.230 --> 07:02.256
RUTH, HOW ARE YOU
HOLDING UP ?

07:02.260 --> 07:04.148
I'M DOING OKAY,
FATHER.

07:04.160 --> 07:06.390
EACH DAY IT'S JUST
A LITTLE BIT EASIER.

07:06.400 --> 07:07.753
THAT'S WHAT
I LOVE HEARING.

07:07.760 --> 07:10.593
WOW, WHAT
A SMALL WORLD !

07:10.600 --> 07:12.192
DO YOU GO
TO THIS CHURCH ?

07:12.200 --> 07:13.827
I JUST JOINED,
I WAS RAISED CATHOLIC,

07:13.830 --> 07:16.458
SO, I LIKE THE WHOLE
RITUAL PART OF IT.

07:16.460 --> 07:18.348
OOH, YOU SMELL GOOD,
WHAT IS THAT ?

07:18.360 --> 07:20.089
WHO ARE YOU ?

07:20.100 --> 07:23.922
OH MY GOD, I CAN'T BELIEVE
I NEVER INTRODUCED MYSELF.

07:23.930 --> 07:25.727
IT SEEMS LIKE WE'VE KNOWN
EACH OTHER FOREVER.

07:25.730 --> 07:28.358
I'M TRACY MONTROSE BLAIR.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.827
HI, I'M DAVID--

07:29.830 --> 07:31.491
FISHER, I KNOW,
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

07:31.500 --> 07:33.229
OKAY, WHY ?

07:33.230 --> 07:35.790
BECAUSE MY UNCLE WALT WAS BURIED
AT YOUR FUNERAL HOME.

07:35.800 --> 07:38.052
OLD GUY ?

07:38.060 --> 07:39.755
CANCER ?

07:39.760 --> 07:42.126
HAD A TATTOO OF
A ROULETTE WHEEL
ON HIS BACK ?

07:42.130 --> 07:43.495
OH, YES.

07:43.500 --> 07:45.127
I HAVE A TATTOO.

07:45.130 --> 07:47.223
A BUTTERFLY.

07:47.230 --> 07:51.291
I THINK THAT YOU SHOULD KNOW
THAT I'M NOT REALLY AVAILABLE.

07:51.300 --> 07:52.619
YOU HAVE
A GIRLFRIEND ?

07:52.630 --> 07:54.154
YES.

07:54.160 --> 07:55.525
SERIOUS ?

07:55.530 --> 07:57.555
WE'RE ENGAGED.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.596
WELL...
GOOD FOR YOU.

07:59.600 --> 08:02.296
MOST MEN YOUR AGE

08:02.300 --> 08:04.495
ARE SO COMMITMENT-FOBIC
IT'S PATHETIC.

08:04.500 --> 08:05.956
YES, MEN ARE PIGS.

08:05.960 --> 08:07.450
OR THEY'RE GAY.

08:07.460 --> 08:10.429
WELL, I'M CERTAINLY GLAD
TO FIND OUT YOU'RE NOT GAY.

08:10.430 --> 08:12.557
I HAVE TO GO,
MY MOTHER'S WAITING.

08:15.160 --> 08:16.297
( Tracy )
BYE BYE !

08:16.300 --> 08:18.052
SHE SEEMS NICE.

08:18.060 --> 08:20.790
SHE SEEMS NUTS.

08:31.100 --> 08:32.556
HELLO ?!

08:32.560 --> 08:35.950
( female )
OUT HERE !

08:38.230 --> 08:39.788
HEY.

08:39.800 --> 08:41.427
THIS IS
THE LIFE, HUH ?

08:41.430 --> 08:42.988
APPARENTLY.

08:43.000 --> 08:44.991
SO, HOW OFTEN DO
MOMMY AND DADDY GO AWAY ?

08:45.000 --> 08:46.422
OH, CONSTANTLY.

08:46.430 --> 08:47.897
THEY'RE VERY
IMPORTANT PEOPLE

08:47.900 --> 08:49.856
WITH VERY IMPORTANT
PLACES TO GO.

08:49.860 --> 08:53.125
LUCKY FOR THEM I HAVE
ABSOLUTELY NOWHERE TO GO.

08:53.130 --> 08:55.621
HOW ARE YOU ?

08:55.630 --> 08:56.892
I'M GOOD.

08:56.900 --> 08:58.026
IT'S CHILLY TODAY,
AREN'T YOU COLD ?

08:58.030 --> 08:59.019
NOPE.

09:02.030 --> 09:03.520
JESUS, IT'S LIKE
A HOT TUB IN HERE.

09:03.530 --> 09:05.589
MOMMY AND DADDY KEEP IT
THIS HOT ALL THE TIME.

09:05.600 --> 09:07.022
EVEN IN SUMMER.

09:07.030 --> 09:09.225
THEY'RE VERY WASTEFUL.

09:09.230 --> 09:12.393
AH, THAT'S JUST WRONG.

09:20.200 --> 09:22.623
( Nate )
OH, MAN, YOU ARE...

09:22.630 --> 09:24.427
WHAT ?

09:24.430 --> 09:27.797
YOU'RE UNLIKE ANY WOMAN
I'VE EVER MET.

09:27.800 --> 09:29.495
GOOD.

09:38.760 --> 09:40.694
YOU SCARE ME
A LITTLE.

09:40.700 --> 09:42.224
WHY ?

09:44.300 --> 09:45.699
I DON'T KNOW.

09:45.700 --> 09:47.793
IT'S JUST, UH...

09:47.800 --> 09:51.019
SO MUCH I DON'T
KNOW ABOUT YOU.

09:52.360 --> 09:53.622
ME?

09:53.630 --> 09:57.999
I AM AN OPEN BOOK.

10:12.700 --> 10:15.225
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE BRINGING
YOUR FRIENDS HOME.

10:15.230 --> 10:17.027
YOU KNOW, YOU HAVEN'T
DONE THAT IN YEARS.

10:17.030 --> 10:18.793
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE ?

10:18.800 --> 10:20.290
YOU SAID YOU'D BE GONE
THROUGH THE WEEKEND.

10:20.300 --> 10:21.790
YES, IT'S SUNDAY.

10:21.800 --> 10:23.324
IT'S THE END
OF THE WEEKEND.

10:23.330 --> 10:26.493
NATE, THESE ARE
MY PARENTS,

10:26.500 --> 10:29.822
MARGARET AN D
BERNARD CH ENOWITH.

10:29.830 --> 10:32.298
MARGARET AND BERNARD,
THIS IS NATE FISHER,

10:32.300 --> 10:34.928
THE MAN I AM
HAVING SEX WITH.

10:36.160 --> 10:37.593
HELLO.

10:37.600 --> 10:40.854
BRENDA HAS TOLD US
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING ABOUT YOU.

10:40.860 --> 10:43.852
YOU KNOW WHAT ?
I'M NOT SURPRISED.

10:43.860 --> 10:45.418
I'M NOT SURE THERE'S
THAT MUCH TO TELL.

10:45.430 --> 10:46.897
OH, DON'T BE
SO MODEST.

10:46.900 --> 10:49.994
NATE'S STUDYING FOR HIS
FUNERAL DIRECTORS' LICENSE.

10:50.000 --> 10:52.798
WELL, NATE, YOU'LL HAVE TO
TELL US ALL ABOUT THAT.

10:52.800 --> 10:54.791
WILL YOU
STAY FOR LUNCH ?

10:54.800 --> 10:56.358
AT LEAST
A DRINK OR TWO ?

10:56.360 --> 10:58.248
I'D LIKE TO, BUT--

10:58.260 --> 11:01.593
I REALLY
HAVE TO STUDY.

11:04.230 --> 11:05.424
WELL THEN,

11:05.430 --> 11:08.490
YOU'LL HAVE TO JOIN US
FOR DINNER SOMETIME.

11:08.500 --> 11:09.649
AH...

11:09.660 --> 11:11.821
SOUNDS GREAT.

11:14.360 --> 11:16.021
( Nate )
GREAT !

11:20.200 --> 11:22.054
OKAY,
MRS. FISHER.

11:22.060 --> 11:24.528
I ASKED YOU HERE TODAY
SO WE COULD

11:24.530 --> 11:28.955
TALK ABOUT YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH CLAIRE.

11:28.960 --> 11:30.757
I TOLD HER
IT WASN'T MY IDEA.

11:30.760 --> 11:31.988
NO.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.753
CLAIRE FEELS THAT BEING
THE YOUNGEST CHILD,

11:34.760 --> 11:37.354
PERHAPS SHE MIGHT'VE
MISSED OUT

11:37.360 --> 11:39.828
ON A TIME WHEN
THE FAMILY WAS HAPPIER.

11:39.830 --> 11:41.923
NO, YOU SAID THAT,
I TOLD YOU,

11:41.930 --> 11:44.558
I DON'T THINK THERE WAS A TIME
THIS FAMILY WAS EVER HAPPY.

11:44.560 --> 11:46.050
THAT IS NOT TRUE.

11:46.060 --> 11:48.426
THERE WAS
LOTS OF HAPPINESS

11:48.430 --> 11:49.897
WHEN THE BOYS
WERE YOUNG.

11:49.900 --> 11:52.198
WHEN YOU WERE
YOUNG, CLAIRE.

11:52.200 --> 11:54.919
YOU WERE A VERY HAPPY
LITTLE GIRL, AND YOU KNOW IT.

11:54.930 --> 11:57.819
THAT'S BECAUSE I WAS TOO YOUNG
TO REALIZE WHAT FREAKS WE WERE.

11:57.830 --> 12:00.219
WHY WOULD YOU COME INTO
THIS MAN'S OFFICE

12:00.230 --> 12:01.891
AND TELL HIM
WE WERE NEVER HAPPY ?

12:01.900 --> 12:03.424
I DON'T KNOW,
BECAUSE I GREW UP IN A HOUSE

12:03.430 --> 12:04.954
THAT WAS USUALLY FILLED
WITH TOTAL STRANGERS

12:04.960 --> 12:06.427
WHO WERE CRYING
ALL THE TIME ?

12:06.430 --> 12:07.920
OH, BOO HOO.

12:07.930 --> 12:10.819
I GREW UP
IN A TWO-ROOM APARTMENT
OVER A BARBER SHOP.

12:10.830 --> 12:13.651
AND I SPENT MY TEEN-AGE YEARS
TAKING CARE OF MY GRANDMOTHER

12:13.660 --> 12:15.799
AFTER ONE OF AND THEN BOTH
OF HER LEGS WERE AMPUTATED.

12:15.800 --> 12:16.949
LIFE'S HARD !

12:16.960 --> 12:18.154
MRS. FISHER--

12:18.160 --> 12:19.798
YOU HAD A ROOF OVER YOUR HEAD,
YOU DIDN'T GO HUNGRY.

12:19.800 --> 12:21.051
SHE GETS UP
ON THIS CROSS,

12:21.060 --> 12:22.925
AND THEN THERE'S JUST
NO TALKING TO HER.

12:22.930 --> 12:24.989
YOU DID NOT HAVE TO GO
BEGGING FOR FOOD

12:25.000 --> 12:26.558
ON THE STREETS
OF CALCUTTA.

12:26.560 --> 12:28.323
BECAUSE I WASN'T DROPPED
IN A DUMPSTER SOMEWHERE,

12:28.330 --> 12:30.218
I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO
WANT THINGS TO BE BETTER ?

12:30.230 --> 12:32.448
THIS IS GOOD,
THIS IS GOOD

12:32.460 --> 12:34.394
FOR YOU TWO
TO TALK LIKE THIS.

12:34.400 --> 12:37.221
THESE ARE OBVIOUSLY
THINGS YOU NEED TO SAY.

12:37.230 --> 12:40.597
SO, WE'RE JUST SUPPOSED TO FIGHT
AND GET ON EACH OTHER'S NERVES ?

12:40.600 --> 12:42.795
I PREFER THE NOT
TALKING THING.

12:42.800 --> 12:45.223
I THINK YOU SHOULD TRY TO
HAVE MORE OF A DIALOGUE.

12:45.230 --> 12:48.688
MAKE TIME FOR IT,
SCHEDULE IT.

12:48.700 --> 12:51.225
REMEMBER, ANY
RELATIONSHIP IS WORK.

12:53.730 --> 12:56.255
OKAY, EXCELLENT SESSION.

12:56.260 --> 12:58.626
THAT'S IT ?

12:58.630 --> 13:00.689
THAT'S UP TO YOU,
ISN'T IT ?

13:03.300 --> 13:06.121
HE DOES THIS FOR LIKE
FIVE DIFFERENT SCHOOLS.

13:08.160 --> 13:11.095
SHE SHOULD LOOK
SPECTACULAR.

13:11.100 --> 13:13.523
THAT'S THE MOST
IMPORTANT THING.

13:13.530 --> 13:16.454
WE'LL MAKE SURE THAT
SHE LOOKS HER BEST.

13:16.460 --> 13:20.191
SHE WAS THE REAL DEAL,
YOU KNOW ?

13:20.200 --> 13:22.452
SHE WAS A STAR.

13:22.460 --> 13:26.453
AND I CAN ASSURE YOU
WE WILL GIVE HER A FUNERAL

13:26.460 --> 13:28.325
