I MISSED THOSE.

14:34.900 --> 14:36.595
THIS CHICK
FUCKED A SNAKE.

14:36.600 --> 14:38.852
THIS CHICK FUCKED LIKE
30 GUYS AT ONE TIME.

14:38.860 --> 14:40.623
I SAW THAT,
I SAW THAT !

14:40.630 --> 14:42.723
MY COUSIN RAMONE SHOWED ME
WHEN I WAS LIKE 12

14:42.730 --> 14:44.721
ON THE DIVING BOARD, OKAY ?

14:44.730 --> 14:46.152
THEY WERE LIKE
WRAPPED AROUND THE POOL.

14:46.160 --> 14:47.650
DID YOU SEE THE ONE
WHERE THE GUY'S

14:47.660 --> 14:49.218
RIDING THIS MOTORCYCLE
THAT SHE'S STRAPPED TO

14:49.230 --> 14:51.118
SO HE'S FUCKING HER WHEN
HE'S RIDING AROUND IN CIRCLES ?

14:51.130 --> 14:52.358
HOLY SHIT !

14:53.430 --> 14:55.921
COULD I SPEAK TO YOU
OUTSIDE FOR A MINUTE ?

15:04.460 --> 15:05.950
DAMNIT, NATE.

15:05.960 --> 15:08.724
THE WOMAN ON THAT TABLE IS
JUST AS DESERVING OF DIGNITY

15:08.730 --> 15:10.459
AS ANYONE ELSE
WE PREPARE.

15:10.460 --> 15:13.099
AND FEDERICO
IS AN EMPLOYEE.

15:13.100 --> 15:15.295
IT'S UP TO YOU AND ME TO SET
AN EXAMPLE FOR HIM, ALRIGHT ?

15:15.300 --> 15:17.598
ALRIGHT, I'M SORRY.

15:17.600 --> 15:18.851
SHOW SOME RESPECT.

15:18.860 --> 15:21.249
THESE ARE HUMAN LIVES
WE'RE DEALING WITH HERE.

15:21.260 --> 15:22.557
THESE ARE NOT
ORGANIC BLACKBERRIES

15:22.560 --> 15:24.050
OR GRANOLA IN BULK.

15:24.060 --> 15:25.618
I SAID I'M SORRY.

15:25.630 --> 15:27.029
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE SORRY.

15:27.030 --> 15:29.419
I WANT YOU TO REMEMBER THAT
WHAT WE DO HERE IS SERIOUS.

15:29.430 --> 15:30.988
BECAUSE IT REALLY
SUCKS FOR ME

15:31.000 --> 15:32.922
ALWAYS HAVING TO BE
THE SPOILSPORT.

15:32.930 --> 15:34.056
OKAY.

15:34.060 --> 15:36.051
THANK YOU.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.792
( phone )

15:43.600 --> 15:45.090
HELLO ?

15:45.100 --> 15:46.897
Nate, Bernard Chenowith.

15:46.900 --> 15:48.197
HI.

15:48.200 --> 15:49.724
MARGARET AND I WERE
WONDERING IF YOU WOULD

15:49.730 --> 15:51.823
JOIN US FOR DINNER
TOMORROW NIGHT.

15:51.830 --> 15:53.991
TELL HIM WE'RE NOT GONNA
TAKE NO FOR AN ANSWER.

15:54.000 --> 15:55.490
YOU HEAR THAT ?

15:55.500 --> 15:58.151
Actually I have a lot of
studying to do for this exam--

15:58.160 --> 15:59.821
NATE...

15:59.830 --> 16:03.095
WE'D REALLY LOVE TO BE ABLE TO
GET A SENSE OF WHO YOU ARE

16:03.100 --> 16:05.625
and I'm sure you're curious
about us as well, right ?

16:05.630 --> 16:07.222
Good.

16:07.230 --> 16:09.152
SHALL WE SAY
SEVEN-ISH ?

16:09.160 --> 16:11.196
CAN I BRING
ANYTHING ?

16:12.860 --> 16:14.293
HELLO ?

16:15.660 --> 16:18.549
( loud video game noises )

16:23.360 --> 16:25.328
SUCK ON THAT,
YOU UGLY FUCK.

16:33.830 --> 16:35.024
HI.

16:35.030 --> 16:36.657
THERE'S THIS THING
CALLED KNOCKING.

16:36.660 --> 16:39.220
IT'S LIKE PROTECTED
IN THE FIRST AMENDMENT.

16:39.230 --> 16:41.027
I RENTED
SOME VIDEOS.

16:41.030 --> 16:44.454
I THOUGHT YOU AND I COULD
WATCH THEM TONIGHT.

16:46.730 --> 16:48.129
REMEMBER WHEN YOU WERE
IN MIDDLE SCHOOL

16:48.130 --> 16:50.223
YOU AND I USED TO GO TO
THE MOVIES EVERY MONDAY NIGHT ?

16:50.230 --> 16:52.858
REMEMBER HOW MUCH
FUN WE HAD ?

16:52.860 --> 16:56.193
I REMEMBER SEEING A LOT
OF REALLY BAD MOVIES.

16:59.800 --> 17:01.449
WHAT'D YOU GET ?

17:01.460 --> 17:03.690
"RU NAWAY BRIDE"

17:03.700 --> 17:06.498
AND "THE NUTTY PROFESSOR".

17:10.200 --> 17:11.622
COOL.

17:13.600 --> 17:16.899
02 didn't make
you a bitch.

17:16.900 --> 17:19.460
You were born one.

17:19.460 --> 17:21.951
( laughing )

17:26.300 --> 17:28.291
IT'D BE GOOD
FOR BUSINESS TOO.

17:28.300 --> 17:29.790
DAD WAS
A DEACON THERE.

17:29.800 --> 17:33.292
IT'S A BIG CONGREGATION,
PEOPLE DIE.

17:33.300 --> 17:35.621
THEIR FAMILIES DON'T
KNOW WHERE TO GO

17:35.630 --> 17:37.120
AND THE CHURCH
SENDS THEM OUR WAY.

17:37.130 --> 17:38.688
THEY KNOW
YOU'RE GAY ?

17:38.700 --> 17:42.056
I THINK FATHER JACK
HAS A PRETTY GOOD IDEA.

17:42.060 --> 17:44.995
YOU THINK
HE LIKES YOU ?

17:45.000 --> 17:46.399
KEITH.

17:48.160 --> 17:51.220
DOES THIS MEAN YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BE GOING TO CHURCH
WITH ME ANYMORE ?

17:52.660 --> 17:54.218
WELL, IF THEY
MAKE ME A DEACON,

17:54.230 --> 17:56.755
I'D HAVE TO GO THERE
ALL THE TIME, YEAH.

17:59.800 --> 18:01.654
I'M SORRY,
I KNOW,

18:01.660 --> 18:04.891
SUNDAYS HAVE SORT OF
BEEN OUR DAY.

18:08.160 --> 18:09.991
I THINK IT'S GREAT.

18:10.000 --> 18:12.059
I REALLY DO.

18:12.060 --> 18:13.721
ONE OF THE THINGS
I LOVE ABOUT YOU

18:13.730 --> 18:17.291
IS THE FACT THAT YOUR RELIGION
MEANS SO MUCH TO YOU.

18:17.300 --> 18:19.518
BESIDES I THINK IT COULD BE
KIND OF HOT, YOU KNOW ?

18:19.530 --> 18:22.055
DATING A MAN
OF THE CLOTH ?

18:26.600 --> 18:28.818
BUT I NEED YOU TO DO
SOMETHING FOR ME.

18:28.830 --> 18:30.593
WHAT IS IT, MY SON ?

18:30.600 --> 18:33.899
YOU KNOW THE GAY FIREMEN
AND POLICE OFFICERS CLUB

18:33.900 --> 18:35.128
I BELONG TO ?

18:35.130 --> 18:37.394
WE'RE HAVING A PARTY
IN LAGUNA THIS WEEKEND.

18:37.400 --> 18:39.288
I WANT YOU
TO BE MY DATE.

18:39.300 --> 18:41.291
YOUR DATE,
WILL I GET A CORSAGE ?

18:41.300 --> 18:43.996
I WANT YOU TO START MEETING
SOME OF MY FRIENDS, DAVID.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.855
I'D LIKE THAT.

18:48.260 --> 18:49.727
OH.

18:49.730 --> 18:51.027
FORGIVE ME, FATHER.

18:51.030 --> 18:53.954
FOR I AM
ABOUT TO SIN.

18:59.000 --> 19:01.321
(flatulating on tv)

19:03.400 --> 19:06.255
( laughing )

19:09.800 --> 19:12.553
THIS IS AN ENTIRE MOVIE
ABOUT EXPELLING GAS.

19:12.560 --> 19:15.324
I THINK THAT'S
WHY PEOPLE LIKE IT.

19:17.360 --> 19:19.453
I DON'T WANT
TO WATCH THIS.

19:19.460 --> 19:21.394
GOOD, 'CAUSE
NEITHER DO I.

19:31.330 --> 19:33.150
CLAIRE, LOOK...

19:34.500 --> 19:37.025
I KNOW YOU PROBABLY
THINK I'M OLD AND STUPID.

19:37.030 --> 19:39.089
NO, MOM, I DON'T.

19:39.100 --> 19:41.694
BUT I LOVE YOU JUST
AS MUCH AS I EVER DID.

19:41.700 --> 19:43.497
AND I'M WORRIED
ABOUT YOU

19:43.500 --> 19:45.229
AND I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO HELP.

19:45.230 --> 19:46.925
I DON'T NEED HELP.

19:46.930 --> 19:49.251
WHY IS EVERYONE ACTING LIKE
I'M IN THE TRENCHCOAT MAFIA ?

19:49.260 --> 19:51.023
YOU STOLE A FOOT.

19:51.030 --> 19:52.258
A HUMAN FOOT !

19:52.260 --> 19:54.319
OKAY, YOU WANT
TO KNOW WHY ?

19:54.330 --> 19:56.924
BECAUSE SOME GUY
WHO TOTALLY SCAMMED ME
INTO HAVING SEX WITH HIM

19:56.930 --> 19:59.296
BECAUSE I THOUGHT
HE ACTUALLY CARED ABOUT ME,

19:59.300 --> 20:01.621
HE TOLD THE ENTIRE SCHOOL
THAT I SUCKED HIS TOES.

20:01.630 --> 20:03.291
AND THEN WHEN I
CONFRONTED HIM ABOUT IT,

20:03.300 --> 20:04.995
HE SHOWED
ENTIRELY NO REMORSE.

20:05.000 --> 20:06.558
SO, I SAW NATE DROP
THE FOOT ON THE FLOOR

20:06.560 --> 20:08.994
I JUST GRABBED IT, JUST TO GET
BACK AT THAT ASSHOLE, OKAY ?

20:09.000 --> 20:11.218
IT WASN'T PREMEDITATED,
I'M NOT JEFFREY DAHMER.

20:11.230 --> 20:13.448
I DON'T GET OFF ON
HACKED-UP BODY PARTS.

20:13.460 --> 20:14.893
YOU'RE HAVING SEX ?

20:14.900 --> 20:16.697
NO.

20:16.700 --> 20:18.156
JESUS.

20:18.160 --> 20:20.128
NO, I'M SORRY, I CANNOT HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION WITH YOU.

20:20.130 --> 20:21.757
AND I'M REALLY SORRY,

20:21.760 --> 20:23.296
BUT I DON'T THINK WE'RE EVER
GONNA HAVE ONE OF THESE

20:23.300 --> 20:25.154
LIKE TOUCHY-FEELY
MOTHER-DAUGHTER RELATIONSHIPS

20:25.160 --> 20:27.094
LIKE YOU SEE ON TV
AND IN THE MOVIES

20:27.100 --> 20:29.523
BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT,
THEY DON'T EXIST !

20:36.000 --> 20:39.026
AH, HERE'S OUR GUEST,

20:39.030 --> 20:42.659
AND HE BROUGHT US A BOTTLE OF
LOUIS JADOT PINOT NOIR.

20:42.660 --> 20:45.652
1997, NO LESS.

20:45.660 --> 20:46.991
OKAY,

20:47.000 --> 20:48.956
A MAN WHO
KNOWS HIS WINE.

20:48.960 --> 20:51.019
I'M LIKING YOU
MORE AND MORE, NATE.

20:51.030 --> 20:54.124
WELL, I WORKED AT A FOOD CO-OP
IN SEATTLE FOR A LONG TIME.

20:54.130 --> 20:55.825
LEARNED A LITTLE BIT.

20:55.830 --> 20:58.856
A CO-OP, SO THERE'S A LITTLE
HIPPY IN THERE, HUH ?

20:58.860 --> 21:00.157
THAT MAKES SENSE.

21:00.160 --> 21:02.025
BRENDA WOULD FIND
THAT ATTRACTIVE.

21:02.030 --> 21:05.124
SHE LIKES TO THINK OF
HERSELF AS BEING WILDLY
COUNTER-CULTURAL.

21:05.130 --> 21:08.019
I THINK SHE'S ACTUALLY
JUST JEALOUS OF THE FACT

21:08.030 --> 21:10.828
THAT BERN AND I REALLY
WERE HIPPIES...

21:10.830 --> 21:11.899
BRIEFLY.

21:11.900 --> 21:13.253
CAN I OFFER
YOU A DRINK ?

21:13.260 --> 21:15.023
SURE, DO YOU HAVE
ANY BEER ?

21:15.030 --> 21:19.228
NO, WE HAVE VODKA,
SCOTCH, BOURBON.

21:19.230 --> 21:20.993
I'LL HAVE
A LITTLE BOURBON.

21:21.000 --> 21:22.524
MAN LY, BUT NOT
ELITIST.

21:22.530 --> 21:24.225
JUST HER TYPE.

21:24.230 --> 21:25.959
DOWN, GIRL.

21:27.260 --> 21:29.649
SO, WHERE IS BRENDA ?

21:29.660 --> 21:31.924
BRENDA.

21:31.930 --> 21:34.057
OH, BRENDA'S NOT
COMING TONIGHT.

21:37.100 --> 21:39.056
REALLY ?

21:39.060 --> 21:42.257
WELL, SHE FELT, AND I REALLY
HAVE TO AGREE WITH HER

21:42.260 --> 21:44.251
THAT WE'D HAVE A MUCH
BETTER CHANCE

21:44.260 --> 21:47.252
OF GETTING TO KNOW EACH OTHER
IF SHE WEREN'T HERE.

21:47.260 --> 21:50.798
SHE DOES TEND TO TAKE
CENTER STAGE, SO TO SPEAK.

21:51.760 --> 21:53.125
HUH.

21:53.330 --> 21:56.527
I KIND OF WISH SOMEBODY THOUGHT
TO TELL ME ABOUT THIS.

21:56.530 --> 21:58.919
I'M SORRY,
I ASSUMED SHE DID.

22:06.500 --> 22:08.855
THERE YOU ARE.

22:10.030 --> 22:11.327
( male )
DAVID WAS RAISED
IN THIS CHURCH.

22:11.330 --> 22:12.957
HE WAS CHRISTENED
AND CONFIRMED HERE.

22:12.960 --> 22:14.518
HE SERVED AS
AN ALTER BOY.

22:14.530 --> 22:18.318
AND HE WAS PRESIDENT OF THE
YOUTH MINISTRY IN HIGH SCHOOL.

22:18.330 --> 22:20.753
HOW OLD ARE YOU,
DAVID ?

22:20.760 --> 22:22.091
I'M 31.

22:22.100 --> 22:24.728
WHAT DO YOU DO
FOR A LIVING ?

22:24.730 --> 22:26.789
I'M A FUNERAL DIRECTOR.

22:26.800 --> 22:28.097
AH...

22:28.100 --> 22:30.250
HIS FATHER SERVED AS
A DEACON FOR OVER A DECADE.

22:30.260 --> 22:32.751
HE JUST RECENTLY
PASSED AWAY.

22:32.760 --> 22:36.423
SO, YOU SEE THIS AS A SORT OF
PASSING THE TORCH.

22:36.430 --> 22:40.298
NO, SIR, I SEE IT AS
A CHANCE TO SERVE GOD.

22:41.260 --> 22:42.124
WELL,

22:42.130 --> 22:43.791
I'M GLAD TO
HEAR YOU SAY THAT.

22:43.800 --> 22:45.654
BECAUSE THAT'S
WHAT IT IS.

22:45.660 --> 22:49.653
BEING A DEACON IS MORE
THAN JUST HAVING ACCESS

22:49.660 --> 22:51.093
TO THE CHURCH
MAILING LIST

22:51.100 --> 22:54.194
AND PASSING OUT YOUR
BUSINESS CARDS AFTER MASS.

22:55.860 --> 22:59.853
SIR, I WON'T DENY THAT I RUN
A BUSINESS PROVIDING SERVICE

22:59.860 --> 23:01.691
TO PEOPLE IN
TIMES OF NEED.

23:01.700 --> 23:05.158
BUT I WOULD NEVER EXPLOIT
MY RELATIONSHIP TO THE CHURCH

23:05.160 --> 23:07.196
FOR MARKETING PURPOSES.

23:07.200 --> 23:10.454
FRANKLY, I WOULD CONSIDER THAT
TO BE A PRETTY GRAVE SIN.

23:10.460 --> 23:12.951
NO PUN INTENDED.

23:14.530 --> 23:16.521
ST. BARTHOLOMEW
IS AN OLD CHURCH,

23:16.530 --> 23:19.351
A CONSERVATIVE CHURCH.

23:19.360 --> 23:22.193
CHURCH THAT DOESN'T NEED
TO HAVE ITS BOAT ROCKED.

23:22.200 --> 23:25.499
WHICH IS PRECISELY WHY I FEEL
DAVID IS A GOOD CANDIDATE.

23:25.500 --> 23:28.389
HOW MANY MEN HIS AGE HAVE
VALUES AS STRONG AS HIS ?

23:28.400 --> 23:31.153
I THINK HE WOULD BE
AN EXCELLENT ROLE MODEL.

23:32.760 --> 23:34.091
ARE YOU MARRIED ?

23:34.100 --> 23:37.820
NO, SIR, I WAS
ENGAGED, BRIEFLY.

23:42.700 --> 23:45.658
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE YOU'D
LIKE TO TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF

23:45.660 --> 23:47.924
BEFORE I CONSIDER THIS ?

23:47.930 --> 23:49.921
NO, SIR.

23:52.560 --> 23:55.393
IS THERE ANYTHING SPECIFIC ABOUT
ME THAT YOU'D LIKE TO ASK ?

23:55.400 --> 23:56.958
NO.

24:00.830 --> 24:04.948
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
MY DECISION IN A FEW DAYS.

24:09.100 --> 24:10.829
YOU IMPRESSED HIM.

24:10.830 --> 24:12.297
YOU THINK ?

24:12.300 --> 24:13.528
YES.

24:13.530 --> 24:15.919
OH, BY THE WAY,
ONE OF OUR PARISHIONERS

24:15.930 --> 24:17.625
RECENTLY LOST HER FATHER
TO LIVER CANCER,

24:17.630 --> 24:18.824
SHARON MURDOCH.

24:18.830 --> 24:21.253
I GAVE HER YOUR NAME,
YOU MAY BE GETTING A CALL.

24:21.260 --> 24:23.023
THANK YOU.

24:26.530 --> 24:28.794
AGAIN WITH
THE NOT KNOCKING.

24:28.800 --> 24:30.950
PACK SOME THINGS,
WE'RE GOING TO SAN BERNARDINO.

24:30.960 --> 24:32.120
WHAT ?

24:32.130 --> 24:33.654
WE'RE SPENDING THE NIGHT
AT MY COUSIN HANNAH'S.

24:33.660 --> 24:36.049
MOM, I'M DOING
HOMEWORK.

24:36.060 --> 24:37.755
WELL, STOP.

24:37.760 --> 24:40.297
I HAVE SCHOOL
TOMORROW.

24:40.300 --> 24:42.928
I'LL WRITE A NOTE !

24:42.930 --> 24:44.227
( door slamming )

24:45.630 --> 24:47.951
( Margaret)
YOU KNOW, IT'S BEEN
SUCH A LONG TIME

24:47.960 --> 24:50.520
SINCE BRENDA'S WANTED US TO MEET
ANY OF THE MEN IN HER LIFE.

24:50.530 --> 24:52.794
( Bernard )
WHAT WAS THAT LAST ONE,
CHIROPRACT OR ?

24:52.800 --> 24:54.290
HE WAS A ROLFER.

24:54.300 --> 24:55.927
HE WAS AN IDIOT.

24:55.930 --> 24:57.727
WELL, TO BE
PERFECT LY HONEST,

24:57.730 --> 24:59.823
I'M NOT SURE BRENDA EVER
MEANT FOR US TO MEET.

24:59.830 --> 25:00.956
I DON'T THINK SHE REALLY
EXPECTED YOU GUYS

25:00.960 --> 25:02.097
TO COME HOME
THAT DAY.

25:02.100 --> 25:03.624
OH, NATE.

25:03.630 --> 25:06.724
WHERE BRENDA'S CONCERNED,
THERE ARE NO COINCIDENCES.

25:08.460 --> 25:10.394
YOU THINK SHE
PLANNED ALL THIS ?

25:10.400 --> 25:11.856
OF COURSE.

25:11.860 --> 25:14.499
SHE'S A MASTER
MANIPULATOR.

25:14.500 --> 25:15.728
I MEAN,
I LOVE HER DEARLY,

25:15.730 --> 25:18.324
BUT YOU REALLY OUGHT TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GETTING INTO.

25:18.330 --> 25:19.957
NOW, WOULD YOU LIKE
ANOTHER BOURBON ?

25:19.960 --> 25:22.690
NO THANKS.

25:26.200 --> 25:27.929
CAN I ASK YOU
GUYS SOMETHING ?

25:27.930 --> 25:30.524
AS LONG AS IT DOESN'T
INVOLVE ASKING US FOR MONEY.

25:31.530 --> 25:33.691
NO, IT DOESN'T.

25:34.700 --> 25:38.124
DOES THE NAME "NATHANIEL"
HAVE ANY SIGNIFICANCE TO YOU ?

25:42.530 --> 25:43.952
WELL, SURE.

25:43.960 --> 25:46.554
NATHANIEL AND ISABEL.

25:52.930 --> 25:56.024
BRENDA ADORED THESE BOOKS
AS A LITTLE GIRL.

25:56.030 --> 25:57.998
SHE COULD READ BY THE TIME
SHE WAS THREE.

25:58.000 --> 26:00.719
WHAT ARE THEY ABOUT ?

26:00.730 --> 26:03.051
TWO ORPHANS WHO
HAD ADVENTURES.

26:03.060 --> 26:05.597
THEY RAN AWAY
FROM AN ORPHANAGE,

26:05.600 --> 26:09.092
THERE WAS A MALEVOLENT NURSE WHO
WAS ALWAYS HUNTING THEM DOWN.

26:09.100 --> 26:11.489
BUT THEY ALWAYS MANAGED
TO OUTSMART HER.

26:11.500 --> 26:14.594
TYPICAL INFANTILE
WISH FULFILLMENT.

26:15.700 --> 26:18.726
HMM, I'VE NEVER
EVEN HEARD OF 'EM.

26:18.730 --> 26:20.550
THEY'RE BRITISH,
QUITE DARK.

26:20.560 --> 26:22.391
PEOPLE DIE IN THEM
ALL THE TIME.

26:22.400 --> 26:24.356
WHEN BRENDA'S BROTHER
WAS BORN,

26:24.360 --> 26:26.920
WE EXPECTED SERIOUS
DISPLACEMENT ANXIETY FROM HER,

26:26.930 --> 26:28.397
BUT THERE WAS NONE.

26:28.400 --> 26:29.753
SHE WOULD SIT
NEXT TO HIS CRIB

26:29.760 --> 26:31.955
AND READ HIM THESE
STORIES FOR HOURS.

26:31.960 --> 26:34.053
SHE WAS WHAT,
THEN, VERN, FOUR ?

26:34.060 --> 26:35.755
FIVE AT MOST.

26:35.760 --> 26:38.194
IT'S ALL
IN THE BOOK.

26:38.200 --> 26:42.022
THIS BOOK ?

26:44.500 --> 26:48.197
YOU MEAN, SHE DIDN'T TELL YOU
ABOUT THAT EITHER ?

26:53.200 --> 26:54.326
I feel terrible.

26:54.330 --> 26:56.855
I'm sorry I snapped
at Grandma.

26:56.860 --> 26:58.623
Yeah, huh ?

26:58.630 --> 27:01.121
that was a pretty
"Frealq Friday" moment
we had back there.

27:01.130 --> 27:02.654
( laughing )

27:05.460 --> 27:07.792
RUTHIE, I AM SO
GLAD YOU CALLED.

27:07.800 --> 27:10.553
GINNIE AND I WOULD NEVER ALLOW
OURSELVES THIS KIND OF FOOD

27:10.560 --> 27:12.892
UNLESS IT WERE A REALLY
SPECIAL OCCASION.

27:12.900 --> 27:15.255
WE ARE DEFINITELY
GONNA HAVE TO DO

27:15.260 --> 27:16.921
AN EXTRA SPINNING CLASS
THIS WEEK.

27:16.930 --> 27:18.249
TOMORROW MORNING ?

27:18.260 --> 27:19.591
WHO'S TEACHING ?

27:19.600 --> 27:20.624
DEREK.

27:20.630 --> 27:22.291
OOH, I'M SO THERE.

27:22.300 --> 27:25.326
MOM AND I HAVE
THE HUGEST CRUSH

27:25.330 --> 27:26.991
ON THIS SPINNING
INSTRUCTOR AT THE Y.

27:27.000 --> 27:30.254
HE IS HOT, HOT, HOT.

27:32.000 --> 27:33.149
SO...

27:33.160 --> 27:35.025
CLAIRE, HAVE YOU
THOUGHT ABOUT COLLEGE ?

27:35.030 --> 27:36.588
YEAH.

27:36.600 --> 27:40.422
I'D LOVE TO GO TO LIKE
NYU OR COLUMBIA, BUT,

27:40.430 --> 27:42.898
I DON'T KNOW IF
I COULD EVER GET IN.

27:42.900 --> 27:46.358
WELL, THERE ARE SOME
GREAT SCHOOLS IN LA.

27:46.360 --> 27:49.420
WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO GO
TO SCHOOL IN THE SAME TOWN

27:49.430 --> 27:50.897
YOU GREW UP IN ?

27:50.900 --> 27:53.653
I GO TO CAL STATE
RIGHT HERE IN SAN BERDOO.

27:53.660 --> 27:56.299
WELL, WHATEVER
ROCKS YOUR BOAT.

27:56.300 --> 27:57.927
CLAIRE.

27:57.930 --> 27:59.693
HEY.

27:59.700 --> 28:00.849
I LOVE IT.

28:00.860 --> 28:02.293
BY LIVING AT HOME,

28:02.300 --> 28:03.756
I'M SAVING A TON OF MONEY
FOR GRAD SCHOOL.

28:03.760 --> 28:05.352
I'M NOT STUCK
IN SOME CRAPPY DORM

28:05.360 --> 28:07.248
WHERE EVERYONE'S
SMOKING POT

28:07.260 --> 28:09.023
AND PLAYING LOUD MUSIC
ALL THE TIME.

28:09.030 --> 28:12.056
AND I DON'T HAVE TO
CALL CAMPUS POLICE

28:12.060 --> 28:14.051
EVERY TIME I WANT TO
WALK HOME FROM THE LIBRARY

28:14.060 --> 28:16.153
SO THAT
I DON'T GET RAPED.

28:17.200 --> 28:19.191
AND I LIKE TO STAY
CLOSE TO MY MOM.

28:19.200 --> 28:21.350
THAT TRANSLATES INTO
I GET TO DO HER LAUNDRY.

28:21.360 --> 28:23.851
OH, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

28:23.860 --> 28:26.454
I LOVE MY MOM
AND I'M NOT ASHAMED OF IT.

28:26.460 --> 28:28.792
THANK YOU, HONEY,
I LOVE YOU TOO.

28:33.760 --> 28:37.423
OKAY, ANYBODY
WANT MORE ?

28:45.560 --> 28:47.289
SO, HOW WAS IT ?

28:47.300 --> 28:49.052
OH, IT WAS QUITE
IN FORMATIVE.

28:49.060 --> 28:51.096
I KNOW WHAT NATHANIEL
MEANS NOW.

28:51.100 --> 28:53.193
I KNOW YOU HAVE
AN IQ OF 185.

28:53.200 --> 28:55.088
I KNOW YOU HAD A BOOK
WRITTEN ABOUT YOU.

28:55.100 --> 28:57.193
HERE, I SIGNED IT
FOR YOU.

28:58.400 --> 29:00.595
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST
TELL ME ABOUT THIS ?

29:00.600 --> 29:03.398
PEOPLE ALWAYS CHANGE TOWARD ME
AFTER THEY READ IT.

29:03.400 --> 29:05.493
I WAS JUST TRYING TO MAKE
THE FUN PART LAST.

29:05.500 --> 29:07.354
OH, GOD !

29:07.360 --> 29:09.089
SO, YOU'RE KIND OF
SCARILY BRILLIANT,

29:09.100 --> 29:10.499
I CAN HANDLE THAT.

29:10.500 --> 29:13.151
WHAT I CAN'T HANDLE IS THE WAY
YOU KEEP MIND-FUCKING ME

29:13.160 --> 29:14.525
FOR YOUR OWN PERSONAL
ENTERTAINMENT.

29:14.530 --> 29:16.452
AND IT'S REALLY
STARTING TO PISS ME OFF.

29:16.460 --> 29:18.849
WELL, I'M SORRY I'M NOT SOME
WELL-BEHAVED LITTLE NOTHING

29:18.860 --> 29:20.191
THAT NEVER
CHALLENGES YOU,

29:20.200 --> 29:21.599
BUT IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,

29:21.600 --> 29:23.227
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
JUST LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

29:23.230 --> 29:26.324
SO, WHAT, YOU'RE TRYING
TO DRIVE ME AWAY ?

29:26.330 --> 29:29.652
YEAH, NATE, I'M TRYING
TO DRIVE YOU AWAY.

29:35.500 --> 29:38.651
IT WAS MY MOTHER'S IDEA
THAT I NOT BE THERE.

29:38.660 --> 29:42.152
WHICH IS FINE BY ME, I DON'T
REALLY ENJOY THEIR COMPANY.

29:42.160 --> 29:45.152
SHE SAID IT
WAS YOUR IDEA.

29:45.160 --> 29:47.856
YEAH, SHE WOULD.

29:47.860 --> 29:50.590
SHE PROBABLY BELIEVES THAT,
SHE'S OUT OF HER FUCKING MIND.

29:50.600 --> 29:53.194
YOU COULD'VE WARNED ME
WHAT I WAS WALKING INTO.

29:53.200 --> 29:55.259
YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE GONE.

29:55.260 --> 29:58.593
I JUST WANTED TO

